KCNA Blasts U.S. Economic Aggression 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- In the new century the United States revealed its unlimited ambition to put under its control areas rich in oil, gas, diamond and ferrous and nonferrous mineral in the world. This economic aggression sparked ceaseless fratricidal wars in different countries and led to the seizure of territories of other countries and plunder of their people.
 The U.S. is a country which advocates war as it cannot exist without aggression and plunder. 
 One may say the U.S. made its appearance on this earth to swallow up the whole world. That is why it seeks economic profits in the most avaricious and brigandish manner in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Big American monopolies are exercising a great influence on shaping national policies and implementing them in quest of concessions as all economic arteries including industry, transport, post and telecommunications, finance and trade are under their control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The national mechanisms are executing the policies reflecting the interests of these big monopolies, which control both economic arteries and state power, orienting the political situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. considers war and "aid" as two levers for economic plunder.
 Whenever these big monopolies find themselves in an unavoidable chronic economic crisis, they seek a way out of it in the militarization of the economy and arms race.
 U.S. economic "aid" for other countries is another form of aggression under the signboard of "humanitarianism". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the past, multinational corporations of the U.S. made their ways into those developing countries which were suffering economic difficulties under the signboard of "aid." But they reaped profits four or five times and even more than 10 times for every U.S. dollar invested. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the 6th ministerial meeting of the WTO held in late last year the U.S. announced its plan to raise its annual financial assistance to developing countries in trade to 2.7 billion dollars from 1.3 billion dollars by 2010. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the world public put it, this is nothing but "a relief fund with strings attached." 
 The true aim sought by the U.S. is to realize an unlimited overseas expansion of its monopoly capital and put the world economy under its control. 
 The "national security strategy report" formally made public by the U.S. in 2000 called on the U.S. to guide the world and lay groundwork for its security and prosperity in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At that time the U.S. economy was in the grip of an uncontrollable economic crisis caused by serious economic stagnation, sluggish export and increased unemployment, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Much upset by this, the U.S. tried hard to find a way out of the socio-political and economic crisis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the September 11 incident broke out just at the right moment in 2001 the U.S. lost no time to put up the signboard of "anti-terrorism." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It chose Afghanistan and Iraq as the primary targets to implement its scheme.
 The wars proceeded just as it expected. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Munitions companies across the U.S. including four big American munitions corporations: Lockheed Martin, Boeing, Raytheon and T.R.W. operated in full capacity thanks to these new wars. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. oil companies, in the meantime, were free to extract oil from the war-torn countries and oil markets in Mid-east came to be monopolized by big American oil companies such as Exxon Mobil and Chevron-Texaco. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is stretching out its tentacles of economic aggression to all countries and regions of the world to bring greater benefits to its big monopolies.
 The U.S. world strategy is now focused on Asia-Pacific. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. deems it very important for carrying out its strategy to dominate the world to put Asia-Pacific, especially Northeast Asia, which is of great strategic importance and rich in natural resources, under its control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It considers the Korean Peninsula as an important forward strategic strongpoint given the fact that its strategy to dominate the world in the 21st century is to include Northeast Asia in sphere of its influence and put world politics and economy under its control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is the major reason why the U.S. is hyping the "nuclear issue", seeking to internationalize "economic sanctions" against the DPRK and escalating tension on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. "war on terrorism" helped it expand the sphere of its military domination in Asia and secure launching bases in different areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It built military bases in several union republics of the former Soviet Union and even in areas bordering China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. stoked mistrust among countries of the former Soviet Union and sparked civil wars there in a bid to grab oil and gas resources in the region.
 The "war against terrorism" fought by the U.S. forces in the Trans-Caucasian areas and the Black Sea littoral countries is also aimed at grabbing oil in Caspian Sea.
 By intensifying its military inroads into the Black Sea littoral countries the U.S. seeks to draw a line of confrontation from the Black Sea to Central Asia across the Caucasia and thus contain Russia over the issue of strategic resources. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has also expanded its military domination and interference in Africa.
 It has laid springboards from which to perpetrate economic pillage in Asia, Europe, Latin-America, Africa and almost all other areas of the world. 
 What has the U.S. economic aggression brought to the world?
 All those countries and regions that suffered from the U.S. military intervention and its economic plunder are ridden, without exception, with fratricidal wars, domestic conflicts, murder, arson, plunder and all forms of other crimes and social evils.
 The world can never be peaceful as long as the U.S. is allowed to pursue its unlimited ambition to establish an "empire" dominated by its own view on value in the world at the sacrifice of world people and seek its own pleasure and prosperity.
  The world should heighten vigilance against the U.S. economic aggression.
 The U.S.-imposed war crisis and politico-economic chaos is not what humankind is fated to undergo in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. unilateral and arrogant domestic and foreign policies defying the international community are only aggravating its self-contradictions and hastening its self-destruction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the countries and people desirous of peace and progress should take joint actions against the U.S. economic aggression.

National Seminar on Kim Il Sung's Exploits Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A national seminar on the undying feats President Kim Il Sung performed for the revolutionary cause of Juche was held at the People's Palace of Culture on April 5.
 The seminar heard six papers profoundly explaining and proving the undying feats Kim Il Sung performed on behalf of the country and the revolution.
 Candidate Acad., Prof. and Dr. Thae Hyong Chol, president of the Academy of Social Sciences, and Acad., Prof. and Dr. Ji Ki Son, president of Kim Il Sung Military University, and other speakers said the greatest historic feat Kim Il Sung performed for the revolutionary cause of Juche is that he founded the immortal Juche idea, providing a perfect guiding idea for accomplishing the human cause of independence.
 They further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung performed feats for the socialist cause by setting out the Juche- oriented theory of socialism, the theory of man-centered socialism, for the first time in history and firmly adhering to the Juche-oriented stance and revolutionary principles in the whole course of building socialism and thereby building Korean-style socialism on this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important of the immortal feats he performed by providing a military guarantee for accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche is that he founded the unique Songun idea, clearly indicating the way of bolstering the army.
 It is his greatest feat that he put forward Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il as a military genius having personality and qualifications as the brilliant commander of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The whole of Korea is now resounding with patriotic shouts "Korea is one." This is the brilliant fruition of Kim Il Sung's unshakable will for reunification, who consistently adhered to the line of "one Korea," the reunification line, despite any changing situation and dealt hard blows to the separatists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers declared that the army and people of the DPRK would always hold Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the eternal leader of the Party and the people and build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation on this land without fail true to the Songun idea and leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the seminar were Secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea Choe Thae Bok, Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin, officials concerned, officials of the Party and administrative organs and working people's organizations at national levels and in Pyongyang and officials of scientific and educational institutions and Party cadre-training institutions and in the fields of media, literature and arts and the preservation of revolutionary relics.

Celebration Event of Workers and Unionists Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A meeting of workers and other members of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea (GFTUK) was held on the square of the Monument to Party Founding on April 5 to celebrate the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission.
 The reporter and speakers at the meeting noted that the election of Kim Jong Il to the highest post of the Korean revolution provided a sure guarantee for successfully accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche generation after generation and significantly exalted the dignity and might of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has pursued the Songun policy, a socialist political mode, and thus trained the Korean People's Army to be a standard-bearer of the Songun revolution and an invincible army devotedly defending the Party and the leader, the country and socialism and turned the whole country into a impregnable fortress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has wisely led the Workers' Party of Korea, the army and the people with his extraordinary ideological and theoretical wisdom and distinguished political ability, performing undying feats for accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche. These immortal exploits will shine forever in the history of the country along with the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A poem "Song Devoted to the Great Brilliant Commander of Songun" was recited at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were Secretary of the WPK Central Committee Kim Jung Rin, officials of the Central Committee of the GFTUK, officials and members of the GFTUK and working people in Pyongyang.

Egyptian Ambassador Hosts Reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hatter, Egyptian ambassador to the DPRK, gave a reception at the embassy on April 5 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 The ambassador noted that President Kim Il Sung fathered the Juche idea and performed great feats to be always recorded in history in the course of leading the struggle of the Korean people to victory, adding that he is always alive in the hearts not only of the Korean people but of the world progressives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that leader Kim Jong Il has wisely led the Korean people in the drive to build a great prosperous powerful nation true to the lofty intention of the President, the ambassador stressed that the government of Egypt positively backs the struggle of the Korean people for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Dae, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, in a speech said that it is an expression of the profound reverence for the President for the Egyptian friends to join the Korean people in commemorating the Day of the Sun every year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation are the traditional ties provided by President Kim Il Sung and President Mohamed Hosni Mubarak, he stressed that the Korean people would make positive efforts to boost the bilateral ties.
 Present on invitation were Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the staff members of the Egyptian embassy.

Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- "10-Point Programme of the Great Unity of the Whole Nation for the Reunification of the Country", the immortal famous work of President Kim Il Sung published on April 6, Juche 82 (1993) is a great charter of national unity as it fully reflects his idea of great national unity, brilliant wisdom and patriotic will, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 The publication of the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation by the President marked an event which saved the situation that prevailed on the Korean Peninsula at that time from the brink of a nuclear war at one moment and opened up a bright prospect of national unity and reunification, the article says, and goes on:
 The programme has served as a beacon clearly indicating the way of independent reunification and national unity and the most fair and aboveboard one for reunification.
 The programme set forth by the President is a great charter of national unity, the most just and fair one for reunification, as it comprehensively and scientifically clarifies the issues in achieving the great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This programme, first of all, lays it down as the general goal of the great national unity to set up a pan-national unified state which can represent all the members of the nation from every party and faction and of all social standings with the existing two systems and two governments in the north and the south left in tact. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It sets out the idea of unity based on love for the nation and the spirit of national independence. This is a scientific clarification of the ideological basis of the great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President in the programme clarifies all the principles and specific ways for achieving the great national unity such as the issue of achieving unity on the principle of promoting co-existence, co-prosperity and common interests and subordinating everything to the cause of national reunification, the need for the north and the south to put an end to all political disputes that foment division and confrontation between fellow countrymen and trust and unite with each other, the issue of setting store by democracy and joining hands on the road of national reunification without rejecting each other because of difference in isms and the issue of protecting the material and mental wealth of individuals and organizations and encouraging their use for promoting the great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The programme is the most fair and aboveboard charter of the great national unity, the one of national reunification, acceptable to everyone who loves the country and the nation and desires national reunification.

Greening Work Brisk in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A campaign for greening streets, parks and roadsides is being vigorously launched in different provinces, cities and counties across the DPRK when the spring has come.
 In Pyongyang not only employees of institutions and factories but also residents of neighborhood units have turned out in planting good species of roadside trees and flower plants in areas along main streets, parks, recreation grounds and roadsides, adding beauty to the landscape of the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those in North Phyongan Province, setting themselves to plant more than 99 million trees this year, are engaged in transplanting trees in areas along the Paekma-Cholsan Waterway and around Thaechon Power Station No.4 and roadsides in Pakchon, Nyongbyon and Hyangsan Counties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tens of thousands of roadside trees have already been planted in Kumya County, South Hamgyong Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, afforestation work is being done in mountains of different areas of the country on the principle of planting right kinds of trees on right soil.
 In South Phyongan Province, acacia and Evodia Daniellii Benn forests are being created in Phyongsong, Phyongwon, Mundok, Sukchon and Anju areas and larch and pine-nut tree forests in Tokchon, Pukchang, Maengsan and Nyongwon areas.
 Jagang Province plans to plant pine-nut, larch and Populus Canadensis in over 20,000 hectares of mountains this year. And cities and counties of the province including Kanggye City are planting tens of thousands of trees a day. Efforts are being made to create more than 100 hectares of windbreak forests on the table land of Osu Hill in Junggang County. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working people throughout the country are striving hard to plant more trees compared with the last spring when they had transplanted over one billion trees in some 100,000 hectares of land.

24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival under Brisk Preparation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Preparations for the 24th April Spring Friendship Art Festival (April 10-18) are under way at the final stage.
 The preparatory work is being done to suit the coming festival which will be held in a new form. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First of all, the opening ceremony of the festival varies from the past ones. The interior and exterior of the Pyongyang Grand Theater, the venue of the opening ceremony, are bedecked with colorful electric lights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Preparations for the art performance to be given by Korean artists at the opening ceremony, the closing ceremony and the friendly gathering are also being made.
 Nine theaters including the Ponghwa Art Theater, where independent, group and joint performances will be given, have been furnished with new stage settings and lighting fixtures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various kinds of festival posters have been published and festival bulletins will be issued. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Historical and scenic places and cultural institutions in Pyongyang and local areas are ready to receive festival participants and guests.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Chinese Defence Minister
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Thursday met Col. General Cao Gangchuan, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee and vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission of the Communist Party of China, state councilor and minister of National Defense of the People's Republic of China, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall and had a talk with him in a friendly atmosphere. 
 Kim warmly welcomed Cao on a visit to the DPRK at a time when the relations between the DPRK and China are favorably developing thanks to the exchange of visits by the top leaders of the two countries, saying that his current visit to the DPRK marks an important occasion in boosting the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He underscored the need to consolidate these friendly and cooperative relations, adding that the revolutionary armed forces of the two countries have a great tradition whereby they have long maintained close cooperation and strong ties. 
 Cao said that they were deeply impressed by the enthusiastic and friendly hospitality of the Korean comrades while staying in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 China and the DPRK are the friendly neighbors sharing the same mountain and rivers, he said, noting that the Sino-DPRK friendship provided and developed by the leaders of the elder generation have grown stronger than ever before under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the Sino-DPRK relations are blood-sealed ones, he underlined the need to strengthen the solidarity between the armed forces of the two countries no matter how the international situation may change. 
 Kim Jong Gak, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, and general officers and officers of the KPA were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Commander of the Shenyang Military Area of the Chinese People's Liberation Army Chang Wanquan, Assistant to the chief of the CPLA General Staff Zhang Qinsheng, Deputy Commander of the Navy of the CPLA Zhang Yongyi, Deputy Political Commissar of the Air Force of the CPLA Liu Yazhou, Deputy Director of the General Office of the Central Military Commission Cao Yumin and other suite members, Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wu Donghe and Military Attache of the Chinese embassy Yang Xilian.

DPRK Foreign Ministry's Spokesman Slams Japan's Claim to Tok Islet
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry in a statement issued on April 6 accused the Japanese authorities of recently allowing the description of Tok Islet as part of Japan's territory in the history textbooks for high schools after instructing the same thing as regards textbooks for middle schools last year.
 Branding such behavior as an unpardonable shameless act peculiar to Japan, the statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It admits of no argument that the islet belongs to Korea's territory from the historical point of view and in the light of international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the Japanese authorities have obstinately insisted that the islet belongs to Japan's territory. Obviously this is prompted by their wild ambition for aggression and territorial expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is keen to realize its wild ambition of reinvasion, oblivious of the historical lesson drawn from the bitter defeat it suffered after setting out on overseas aggression under the slogan of "The Greater East Asia Co-prosperity Sphere" in the past. 
 Japan keeps tampering with its history and its chief executive continues visiting the "Yasukuni Shrine" despite the unanimous curses and denunciations of the international community including its neighboring countries. All this is mainly attributable to the U.S. backing and patronage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now under strong fire by its neighboring countries for its claims that not only Tok Islet but Diaoyu Islands and the Southern Kurils belong to its territory.
 The historical lesson requires the countries in the region never to allow Japan's wild ambition for territorial expansion but heighten the vigilance against it and jointly react to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality today when there exist close to the DPRK the dangerous bellicose forces getting frantic in their wild ambition for territorial expansion clearly proves once again that Pyongyang was entirely just when it took measures to steadily bolster the military capability for self-defence including nuclear deterrent to defend the peace and security in the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries would be well advised to stop their moves for territorial expansion and racket against the DPRK and the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan that may result in their self-destruction, and behave with discretion, drawing a lesson from history.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Women's Company
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 6 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, inspected a three-revolution red flag women's company of KPA Unit 292.
 He acquainted himself with the company's performance of duty before watching its soldiers' training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about how the company is implementing its training program and set forth tasks to be tackled to put the training on a scientific and regular basis.
 Then he went round an education room, a bedroom, a mess hall, a kitchen, a wash-cum-bath house, a non-staple food store, an outdoor resting place, a barn and other places of the company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance displayed by women soldiers, greatly satisfied to learn that they are leading an affluent life by creating good conditions for their living on their own. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a great success that the commanding officers and soldiers of the company have remarkably increased its combat capability and successfully managed it in perfect unity and brought about a signal turn in the sideline farming, in particular, he said, adding that this radical change clearly shows the unlimited mental power and creative trait of the servicepersons who have taken the lead in cheerfully weathering out such stern trials as "the Arduous March", the forced march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that their noble fighting spirit and trait serve as an example to be followed by the Korean women who like to make a revolution and wage a struggle.
 He spared time to watch an art performance given by servicepersons of the company.
 He gave the servicepersons of the company a pair of binoculars, a machine-gun and an automatic rifle as gifts before having a photo session with them.
 He was accompanied by Hwang Pyong So, vice department director of the WPK Central Committee.
